# Rasyona frontend environment (Vite).
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and override as needed.
# Only VITE_-prefixed vars reach the browser via import.meta.env — never put secrets here.

# --- AG-UI agent endpoints (SSE) ---
# Default "/agui" is a DEV-ONLY proxy prefix. vite.config.ts rewrites it to the backend:
#   /agui/copilot  ->  http://localhost:8000/copilot
# The page route stays "/copilot"; "/agui" is only a transport prefix so browser
# navigations to the SPA route "/copilot" are never captured by the proxy.
#
# PRODUCTION: this default only works behind the dev proxy. Either
#   (a) set an absolute URL below AND add that origin to the backend
#       cors.allow_origins (backend/config), or
#   (b) replicate the "/agui" -> backend rewrite in your reverse proxy.
VITE_AGUI_BASE_URL=/agui

# --- REST API (health now; system listing later) ---
# Default "/api" is a DEV-ONLY proxy prefix rewritten to the backend:
#   /api/health  ->  http://localhost:8000/health
VITE_API_URL=/api

# --- Dev-only: backend target for the Vite proxy (read in vite.config.ts, Node-side) ---
# Not VITE_-prefixed on purpose: it must NOT be exposed to the browser bundle.
# DEV_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:8000
